    dc:creator "Greenbaum, Eli; Allen, Kaitlin E.; Vaughan, Eugene R.; Pauwels, Olivier S. G.; Wallach, Van; Kusamba, Chifundera; Muninga, Wandege M.; Aris- Tote, Mwenebatu M.; Mali, Franck M. M.; Badjedjea, Gabriel; Penner, Johannes; Rödel, Mark-Oliver; Rivera, Jacqueline; Sterkhova, Viktoria; Johnson, Grant; Tapondjou, Walter P.; Brown, Rafe M." ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Night stalkers from above: A monograph of Toxicodryas tree snakes (Squamata Colubridae) with descriptions of two new cryptic species from Central Africa" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723026>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723030>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723048>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723046> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723026>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. (A) Herpetologists James Ashe (at left) and C.J.P. Ionides (at right) holding a large Toxicodryas vexator sp. nov. ca. 1965 at Nairobi Snake Park, Kenya. Photo courtesy of Bio-Ken archive and Steve Spawls. (B) Congolese herpetologist Maurice Luhumyo with adult female paratype (UTEP 22195) of Toxicodryas vexator sp. nov. shortly after its capture on 30 August 2007 from Irangi, South Kivu Province, Democratic Republic of the Congo. Photo: E. Greenbaum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4723026/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723030>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A time-calibrated Bayesian phylogeny of Toxicodryas, based on the cyt b and c-mos genes, modified from Allen et al. (in press). Highly supported nodes (posterior probability ≥ 0.9) are denoted with a black circle. Node bars represent 95% confidence intervals. RADseq (2848 loci) phylogenies showed identical topologies. The five clades supported as distinct species by all species-delimitation analyses of Allen et al. (in press) are shown as black, white, and gray rectangles. Toxicodryas adamanteus sp. nov. includes all populations in Central Africa, including Cameroon, Gabon, and Democratic Republic of the Congo. Outgroups not shown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4723030/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723048>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Photos of the holotype of Toxicodryas vexator sp. nov. (UTEP 22196, 1438 mm SVL) from Mulisi, Nzovu Est, Kahuzi-Biega National Park, South Kivu Province, Democratic Republic of the Congo. (A) Entire body in dorsolateral view, (B) entire body in ventral view, (C) entire body in dorsal view, (D) entire body in ventral view including everted hemipenes, (E) head in dorsal view, (F) head in ventral view, (G) head in left lateral view, (H) head in right lateral view. Photos A–B (shortly after capture): G.M. Mitamba; Photos C–H (preserved specimen): E. Vaughan." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4723048/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4723046>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Photos of Toxicodryas vexator sp. nov. in life. (A) adult black phase from Banalia, Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). Photo: K. Mebert, (B) adult black phase from Mityana, Uganda. Photo: M. Berroneau, (C) adult female paratype (UTEP 22195) from Irangi, DRC. Photo: E. Greenbaum, (D) subadult female (RBINS 18994) from Lieki, DRC. Photo: Z. Nagy, (E) juvenile (UTEP 22193) from Nkala, DRC. Photo: E. Greenbaum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4723046/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

